values: I'm kinda disapointed that summer is over. But then again I think I'm coming out of this summer as a different person. I'm not sure what has changed or why but its for the better. Also I didnt get hurt excessively. Thats always a double plus. Even though I didnt have a summer fling I'm still interested in someone so it could still happen. Unlike 95% of my classmates I'm looking forward to going back to school. I miss all of the social events and just hanging out with my friends 24/7. This summer held alot of challenges but thats ok cuz they didnt stop me from having a good time or being who i needed to be. Thanks to all who made my summer so enjoyable and thanks to all who are going to make this year a blast and a year to remember.

My computer finally works!!! I deleted a bunch of crap off of here so now its faster and I'm having less problems. In the near future I will be creating a different acount that will have all updates on my story that I'm going to be writing. So when I figure more out I'll let you know how to check it and  give me ur opinion. Well thats all the lil stuff.... but I need your real opinion on a problem I have. The otherday after church i knew that i was there for a reason but i didnt know what it was. then later that night i came home and was talking to a very close friend of mine. thats when it hit me that i was at the service to hear the anouncment so i could hook my friend up. well i got all excited and started thinking how perfect it was. the only problem is im not sure if its going to because that person has to make it work not me and i dunno if they are going to do that cuz i know they can but they dont have the self esteem to do it. so am i supposed to keep pushing them, or some to a realization that my great inspiration was a dud...
